{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_017kMaD3AGuCAF7PnhyiytEi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011jAJR6oEbtAZ46kVviazir","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"git add src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/durability_soak.rs && git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\ntest(durability): AC-034a/b power-cut harness + AC-034c blocker\n\n`durability_soak.rs` lands the power-cut harness using the test-binary-\nas-victim trick: a `#[ignore]` `_power_cut_victim_entry` test reopens\nthe engine and write-loops microsecond timestamps; the parent re-spawns\nthe test binary with `--exact --ignored` filtering plus an env-var\nsentinel, sleeps a deterministic randomized 30..180ms, and SIGKILLs\nthe child. Per-trial it reopens via `Engine::open`, reads the\nlast-surviving body timestamp, and runs `PRAGMA integrity_check`.\n\nThe harness is gated on `AGENT_LONG=1` per `perf_gates.rs` precedent.\nP-PWR-TRIALS = 100; both AC-034a (integrity_check == \"ok\") and\nAC-034b (lost-commit p99 ≤ 100 ms) assert in the same test so a single\ntrial loop covers both `cargo test ac_034a` and `cargo test ac_034b`\nfilters.\n\nMeasured on the dev runner: 100/100 trials integrity-ok; p99\nlost-commit = 1 ms (well under the 100 ms budget).\n\nAC-034c (OS-crash) lands as an `#[ignore]`d blocker placeholder rather\nthan silently substituting `kill -9` for an OS crash. The required\nKVM image + sysrq trigger fixture (per `dev/acceptance.md` § AC-034c)\ndoes not exist in this repo; the blocker text in the `#[ignore]`\nreason and the Phase 12-D output JSON (blocker-3) defer the wiring to\na follow-up 12-D-OS-CRASH slice.\nEOF\n)\"","description":"Commit Sub-2"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":467,"cache_read_input_tokens":187767,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":467},"output_tokens":68,"servi